Actor Alexx Ekubo has fulfilled one of his lifelong dreams by marking the Easter celebration onboard the world’s largest cruise ships. The excited Ekubo, in a post via his Instagram page, confessed he always wanted to be on a cruise ship, sailing around the world while thanking God for the privilege to have his dream fulfilled. He shared several beautiful photos of some of his cruising moments onboard the magnificent “Wonder of the Seas”. Noting how blessed he was, the movie star wrote: “I’ve always wanted to be on a cruise ship & sail around the world, now I’m on the largest cruise ship #WonderOfTheSeas, sailing to a new country. What a life I’ve been given, my God I’m Blessed. Guess what country I’ll be waking up in? Happy Easter.”   Chrisland: 10-year-old not raped, says Wizkid’s…     Flaunting relationships on social media hastens breakup…     Best way to dispose used sanitary pads, by Halima Abubakar   The world’s largest cruise ship, measuring a staggering 1,188 feet, Royal Caribbean’s Wonder of the Seas was delivered in January, 2022. The 18-deck cruise ship was built at the Chantiers de l’Atlantique shipyard in Saint-Nazaire, France, and has capacity for 6,988 guests and 2,300 crew members. It was billed to begin its maiden voyage from Fort Lauderdale, Florida, to the Caribbean on March 4 but eventually set sail for the first time on Friday, April 15. The Royal Caribbean-owned ship departed from Port Everglades in Fort Lauderdale on a seven-day voyage to the Caribbean. It will visit Labadee, San Juan, Nassau, and Perfect Day at CocoCay an exclusive destination for Royal Caribbean guests.